Title: B 52 Bomber Crashes In Michigan Crew Survives
 A B 52 bomber crashed and burst into flames early today on a runway while practicing touch and go landings at KI Sawyer Air Force Base officials said
The plane normally equipped to carry nuclear bombs crashed about 1 15 am said Lt
George Peck a spokesman for SAC headquarters in Omaha Neb. The crew was practicing landings after a seven hour training flight when it crashed during one of its touch and go approaches Peck said
All three sections of the plane burned on impact said Senior Airman Tim Sanders a base spokesman
The crew members crawled or were helped out of the front section of the aircraft he said
In other accidents involving B 52s a bomber was damaged when a pilot aborted a takeoff and overshot a runway at Castle Air Force Base in central California on Feb. 11
